direct_enhancements.reason: Both methods are part of the iterator pattern and work together to manage the iteration process.
Both methods modify the internal state of the iterator, with reset() setting the index back to the start.
Both methods handle unsupported operations by throwing exceptions.

enhanced_by.reason: The constructor initializes the iterator state, which is necessary before calling next().
hasNext() should be called before next() to ensure there is a next element.
getArray() can be used to verify the array content after calling next().
